4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROHIBITING LOCAL GOVERNMENTS FROM ENACTING OR
5 ENFORCING AN EXTREME RISK PROTECTION ORDER; PROHIBITING LOCAL GOVERNMENTS FROM
6 RECEIVING FUNDS RELATED TO EXTREME RISK PROTECTION ORDERS; AND AMENDING SECTION 7-
7 1-111, MCA.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Legislative finding -- extreme risk protection order prohibition. (1)
12 The legislature finds that extreme risk protection orders violate a person's right to bear arms under the second
13 amendment of the United States constitution and under Article II, section 12, of the Montana constitution.
14 (2) A local government may not:
15 (a) enact, adopt, or implement a resolution, ordinance, rule, regulation, or policy that would have
16 the effect of enforcing an extreme risk protection order against a resident of the state; or
17 (b) accept a grant or other source of funding for the purpose of aiding in the adoption,
18 implementation, or enforcement of an extreme risk protection order.
19 (3) A local government that violates this section is subject to a civil penalty of up to $10,000,
20 payable to the state general fund. Each instance of enforcement or attempted enforcement constitutes a
21 separate offense.
22 (4) (a) As used in this section, "extreme risk protection order" means a directive, also known as a
23 red flag law, that is an executive order or a written order or warrant issued by a judge, magistrate, or other
24 judicial officer, with the primary purpose of reducing the risk of firearm-related death or injury by doing one or
25 more of the following:
26 (i) prohibiting a named individual from having under the individual's custody or control, owning,
27 possessing, or receiving a firearm; or
28 (ii) removing a firearm from or requiring the surrender of a firearm by a named individual.
